The magistrate or praetor appointed a iudex for the trial of the case, and delivered to him a formula determining the question to be decided. The delivery of the formula cum iudicium accipitur was the moment of the litis contestatio, which ended the proceedings in iure. Such formulae were those of Aquilius de dolo malo for the guidance of the iudex in a claim of restitution, where a fraud-had been practised in* a sale or some similar proceeding.
